Japanese Bought Net 229.1 Billion Yen Overseas Debt Last Week

-- B y   T h e r e s a   B a r r a c l o u g h
-- 
2011-04-20T23:54:09Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-20/japanese-bought-net-229-1-billion-yen-overseas-debt-last-week.html
Japanese investors were net
buyers of foreign bonds during the week ended April 15 according to
figures based on reports from designated major investors released by
the Ministry of Finance in  Tokyo .  Japanese investors bought 229.1 billion yen ($2.8 billion)
in overseas bonds and notes, sold 377.4 billion yen in overseas stocks
and bought 38.5 billion yen in overseas short term securities.
That results in a total net sale of 109.9 billion yen.  Foreign investors sold 171.9 billion yen in Japanese bonds,
bought 89.5 billion yen in stocks, and bought 1544.9 billion yen in
short term securities, resulting in a total net purchase of 1462.4
billion yen.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Theresa Barraclough in Tokyo at   tbarraclough@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Marco Babic at   mbabic@bloomberg.net  